Global Funds Sell Net 982 Million Rupees of Indian Derivatives

-- B y   P a r e s h   J a t a k i a
-- 
2011-07-18T03:44:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-18/global-funds-sell-net-982-million-rupees-of-indian-derivatives.html
Global investors sold a net 982
million rupees ($22 million) of Indian equity  derivatives  on
July 15, according to the National Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, rose 1.4 percent to 888.9 billion rupees, or 33.1
percent of the gross market position, according to the
exchangeâ€™s website. Open interest reached a record 1.6 trillion
rupees on Sept. 21.  Foreign funds bought a net 730 million rupees of shares in
the  cash  segment on July 15, according to preliminary data given
by the bourse.  To contact the reporter on this story:
